text:
Donald Trump has won the 2024 Presidential Election. I was dead wrong on my prediction for a Harris Victory. However, my investment portfolio is very happy that I was wrong. 

With the uncertainty of the elections behind us, stocks exploded higher to new highs with the Dow gaining 1,580 points (+3.57%) and the S&P 500 up 146 points (+2.53%). Long Bonds crashed, 10-year Treasury yields and the USD dollar spiked higher pressuring REITs prices downwards.

POSITIVES OF A TRUMP ADMINISTRATION
• Expectation of corporate tax cuts from 20% to 15%. This should boost S&P 500 Earnings Per Share by 4%
• Deregulation of the financial sector, leading to more M&A, IPOs and higher profits for Big Banks. Positive for JPM, BAC, GS etc..
• Deregulation of the Health care sector & Bio tech sector. Positive for big Pharma, managed health care stocks like UNH, ELV etc…
• Companies like ExxonMobil (XOM), Chevron (CVX) are expected to benefit from policies favouring fossil fuels, including deregulation and promotion of domestic energy production.
• Defence contractors are often seen as beneficiaries under Republican administrations. Stocks like Lockheed Martin (LMT), Northrop Grumman (NOC) could see boosts from increased military spending.
• The Federal Trade Commission will be less inclined to pursue antitrust violations & block M&As of Big tech. Positive for GOOGL, MSFT, META, AMZN
• U.S.-focused Small/mid cap companies (IWM, VBK) could benefit from business incentives and tariffs that favour domestic production.

CONCERNS (WHAT COULD GO WRONG)

• Tariffs, deportation of cheap immigrant workers, more aggressive Fed cuts could lead to a resurgence of inflation to 4% to 5%. This could spark further collapse of Treasury Bonds (TLT) and 10-year treasury yields could spike to 5%~7% & this could force the Fed to hike the Fed Funds rate again -> Bear Market
• Magnify unrealized losses on Balance sheets of banks with significant long bond exposure -> banking crisis part 2
• Increased borrowing costs will hit small/mid-caps, highly leveraged companies (i.e. real estate developers, Telcos, Airlines, Manufacturing, Financials, REITs) etc…
• Companies with pricing power, low debt and high levels of cash should be less affected in this negative scenario

text:
THIS ELECTION WAS A RECKONING I CAN’T DISMISS WITHOUT A FINAL WORD:
So, Trump won the Presidency, and the first thing some of his supporters who follow me thought to do was to tag me and make sure I felt the pain of “taking an L” while they celebrate their “win.”  Apparently some folks think he will merely be their President; or do they know something we don’t?   Nevertheless, the last 30+ hours have actually been pretty somber in our household, and have lead to some heartfelt conversations between my wife and me.  This election revealed way more about America than who won.  In an effort to make sure they re-elected a White man, who’s a silver-spoon heir to a fortune, proven liar, narcissist, thrice married, serial adulterer, adjudicated sexual assaulter, and 34-count convicted felon, who will literally say or do any vile thing publicly, he and his supporters attacked a well-educated Black and Indian woman, who worked her way from humble beginnings, through all 3 branches of the United States Government.  They trashed her with as many lies and false narratives as they could conjure up, while calling her every vulgar name possible.  They even convinced many Black people that she wasn’t Black enough for being raised by her Indian mother… and that she wasn’t loyal enough for marrying a Caucasian man and selecting a Caucasian running mate.  To top that off, knowing that enough folks are too ignorant or lazy to fact-check them, they convinced people that she’d done nothing in public service for Black people, and didn’t have a plan to do anything for anyone!

Now, relative to what she’s done, it’s not that hard to research and find that during her time as a DA and AG Kamala literally helped transform the Judicial system in California for the benefit of all, but in particular the exact Black men who were conned into thinking she unfairly targeted them.  She also did her job as a prosecutor of criminals, as she should have.  But, in the process, she put together a rehabilitation program for those in the “system,” helped reduce recidivism, and out of all the false narratives on the number of Black men she jailed for marijuana, only 2 actually served any jail time at all.  Furthermore, Kamala actively put together an opportunity agenda for Black America, along with a very detailed plan of her proposed policies for the betterment of America, while Trump is still unable to even articulate the “concept of a plan” to replace the ACA that he promised his supporters would occur way back during his first term.  Simply put, if you switched the resumes of these two former Candidates, Trump would’ve won by the largest landslide in the history of Presidential elections with her resume, except for the fact that she would’ve never even made it to the ballot with his resume!  So, I wonder are his supporters that ignorant, or do they just think we are?

In sum, she has been just as unappreciated for her hard work for us as the millions of other women in this Country who would dare challenge the power position of the White man!  Yet she has persevered on as a successful public servant, while being unfairly dragged through the mud with false narratives!  I share in the tears my wife has shed over witnessing this over the course of this campaign and the culmination of America’s reckoning.  Yes, we may have made some progress over the last several decades, but the same White Supremacist Strongholds that were birthed within its inception continue their toxic infection today… Patriarchy, misogyny, homophobia, racism, elitism, and xenophobia are still rallying points in this Country under the guise of some form of moral superiority, or in other words, White Nationalism.  White Evangelicals remain a huge faction of the supporters of all of the above.  America has again revealed her true face, and it is an ugly sight!  WE HAVE A LONG WAY TO GO!

THANK YOU for your valiant effort and all you’ve done VP Kamala Harris!🫡
#ThankYouVPKamalaHarris

Interest in the “4B movement” spiked since Kamala Harris’s defeat, with women sharing videos of themselves on social media pledging to commit to its four “no’s” — no sex, no dating or marriage and no having children with men — for the next four years.
In one video shared on TikTok, a young woman pledges to go celibate and encourages others to delete dating apps in order to “exercise sovereignty” over their bodies. “As a woman, my bodily autonomy matters and this is my way to exercise sovereignty over that,” she says.
“So I highly encourage any other women who are single and still care about progressing women’s rights and still fighting for our bodily autonomy to do the same. Delete your dating apps.”The woman also encourages others to seek out their female friends for comfort “if you need somebody to cuddle” and describes the 4B movement, which originated in South Korea, as a “point of inspiration”.
The US election revealed a gender divide in the electorate, with 55 per cent of men turning out for Mr Trump and 53 per cent of women voting for Ms Harris.
The president-elect touted his role in overturning Roe v Wade, a ruling that ended the nationwide right to abortion, throughout his election campaign and has been repeatedly accused of making offensive comments about women.
In response, some have blamed sexism for America’s decision to return Mr Trump to the White House. “Men will always be against women,” read the caption in one TikTok video of a young woman crying in a car, encouraging women to join the 4B movement. “Women are just as capable to be presidents as a man.”In another video, a woman says that “for the next four years I am going to abstain from sex with men”.
A separate video was captioned: “I think it’s time for American women to participate in our own 4B movement.”
Many of the videos addressed concerns over abortion, which was on the ballot in 10 states and was central to the Harris campaign.
“If men won’t respect our bodies, they don’t get access to our bodies,” one woman said. “All I have to say is, good luck getting laid. Especially in Florida, because me and my girlies are participating in the 4B movement.”
